<subSubSection id="6DE16501251AFF9BFF4510F0FC98FDE4" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2544368A251AFF9BFF4510F0FC98FDE4" blockId="15.[178,1085,418,587]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">
Comment: This wing-dimorphic species was previously known to be widespread in 
<collectingCountry id="5DEC761A251AFF9BFF391092FE9FFE79" box="[206,269,448,470]" name="China" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">China</collectingCountry>
, from southern 
<collectingRegion id="E73FF868251AFF9BFE441092FE66FE79" box="[435,500,448,470]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">Gansu</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="E73FF868251AFF9BFDEF1092FDF6FE79" box="[536,612,448,470]" country="China" name="Jiangsu" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">Jiangsu</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="416A4B7B251AFF9BFD831092FC98FE79" author="ASSING V" box="[628,778,448,470]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630" pagination="1 - 29" refId="ref11114" refString="ASSING V. (2013 a): On the Lathrobium fauna of China I. The species of the Qinling Shan, the Daba Shan, and adjacent mountain ranges (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonn Zoological Bulletin 62 (1): 1 - 29." type="journal article" year="2013">ASSING 2013a</bibRefCitation>
, e). The above specimens represent the first record from 
<collectingCountry id="5DEC761A251AFF9BFE23108CFD83FE5C" box="[468,529,478,499]" name="Japan" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">Japan</collectingCountry>
. The currently known distribution is illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F251AFF9BFBF8108CFF53FDBF" captionStart="Map 2" captionStartId="15.[178,223,1531,1551]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,922,1515]" captionTargetId="figure-287@15.[178,1085,922,1515]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Map 2: Distribution of Lathrobium sinense HERMAN in China and Japan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303085" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303085/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">Map 2</figureCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251AFF9BFF3A10A8FE04FDBF" authorityName="HERMAN" authorityYear="2003" box="[205,406,506,528]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinense">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251AFF9BFF3A10A8FE04FDBF" box="[205,406,506,528]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">Lathrobium sinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most likely of Japanese origin, as can be inferred from the observation that closely allied species have been recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="5DEC761A251AFF9BFCDB134AFCF4FD82" box="[812,870,536,557]" name="Japan" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">Japan</collectingCountry>
(see the two following species), but are unknown from 
<collectingCountry id="5DEC761A251AFF9BFDE81367FDC9FDE4" box="[543,603,565,587]" name="China" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="416A4B7B251AFF9BFD9E1367FD6DFDE4" author="ASSING V" box="[617,767,565,587]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630" pagination="1 - 29" refId="ref11114" refString="ASSING V. (2013 a): On the Lathrobium fauna of China I. The species of the Qinling Shan, the Daba Shan, and adjacent mountain ranges (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonn Zoological Bulletin 62 (1): 1 - 29." type="journal article" year="2013">ASSING 2013a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
